sentences: Kirk Windstein (born April 14, 1965) is an American guitarist and singer.
He is a founding member of the sludge metal band Crowbar and a founding member of the heavy metal supergroup Down, playing with them from 1991 to 2013 and later rejoining the band in 2020.
He is a founding member of the sludge metal band Crowbar and a founding member of the heavy metal supergroup Down, playing with them from 1991 to 2013 and later rejoining the band in 2020.
In 2005, Windstein formed Kingdom of Sorrow with Jamey Jasta of Hatebreed.
Their debut album was released in 2008.
Windstein began his musical career in 1985 as a guitarist for a cover band called Victorian Blitz, and in 1988 joined a hardcore punk band called Shell Shock as a vocalist and guitarist.

After the collapse of Shell Shock in 1988 due to the suicide of Hatch, the band enlisted Kevin Noonan and carried on as Aftershock, which played a mixture of hardcore punk and doom metal.
In 1990, they renamed themselves The Slugs, and after a demo in mid-1990, the band collapsed.
Crowbar was originally signed by Mark Nawara to Pavement Music and released their debut album Obedience thru Suffering in 1991.
Windstein's childhood friend Phil Anselmo (who at the time was with Pantera) produced their next effort, a self-titled album released in 1993.
In 2001, Crowbar went on hiatus, because Windstein concentrated on other bands.
Upon Windstein's return, Crowbar released Lifesblood for the Downtrodden in 2005, and two years later released a live DVD called Live: With Full Force.
The band released Sever the Wicked Hand in 2011, Symmetry in Black in 2014, and their latest album, The Serpent Only Lies, in October 2016.

Down released their debut album NOLA via Elektra Records in 1995 with Windstein on guitar and bass, Anselmo on vocals, Pepper Keenan on guitar, and Jimmy Bower (Crowbar, Superjoint Ritual, and Eyehategod) on drums.
Crowbar recorded three albums before Down reunited to release Down II: A Bustle in Your Hedgerow in 2002.

Afterward, both Windstein and Keenan returned to their main bands, thereby allowing Windstein to record Crowbar's Lifesblood for the Downtrodden with Rex Brown on bass, Craig Nunenmacher (Black Label Society and original Crowbar member) on drums and Down producer Warren Riker in early 2005.
In 2007, Down released the album Down III: Over the Under.
They released an EP titled Down IV – Part I in September 2012.
In late 2013, Windstein announced that he is leaving Down to concentrate on Crowbar 'full-time', as the band has its 25 anniversary in 2014.

In 2005, Windstein teamed up with vocalist Jamey Jasta of Hatebreed to form a new side venture called Kingdom of Sorrow.
